@startuml Documents_Sequence
title Documents Module - Document Lifecycle

actor Seller
actor Operator
participant Frontend
participant Backend
participant StorageService
participant Database
participant ExpiryMonitor

== Document Request by Operator ==
Operator -> Backend: tRPC operator.updateDocumentStatus(docId, "requested")
Backend -> Database: Update fizbo_documents.status = "requested"
Database -> Backend: Confirmation
Backend -> Database: Query FizboDocument + Seller contact
Database --> Backend: Return document and seller info
Backend -> NotificationService: Send DOCUMENT_REQUESTED notification
NotificationService --> Seller: Email + WhatsApp: "We requested [document]"

== Seller Uploads Document ==
Seller -> Frontend: Upload document file
Frontend -> Frontend: Validate file size (max 20MB)
Frontend -> Backend: tRPC documents.upload(orderId, docType, file)

Backend -> StorageService: POST /upload to Supabase Storage
StorageService -> StorageService: Store in fizbo-documents bucket
StorageService --> Backend: Return storage_path

Backend -> Database: Create DocumentUpload record
Database --> Backend: Confirmation

Backend -> Database: Update fizbo_documents.status = "pending"
Backend -> Database: Update obtained_at timestamp
Database --> Backend: Confirmation

Backend -> NotificationService: Send DOCUMENT_UPLOADED notification
NotificationService --> Operator: Alert operator to verify

== Operator Verifies Document ==
Operator -> Backend: tRPC operator.updateDocumentStatus(docId, "complete")
Backend -> Database: Update fizbo_documents.status = "complete"
Backend -> Database: Update updated_at timestamp

Backend -> Database: Extract expiry_date (if applicable)
Database --> Backend: Stored expiry info

Backend -> ExpiryMonitor: Create expiry monitoring record
ExpiryMonitor --> Backend: Monitor scheduled

Backend -> NotificationService: Send DOCUMENT_COMPLETE notification
NotificationService --> Seller: Email + WhatsApp: "[Document] is ready"

== Seller Downloads Document ==
Seller -> Frontend: Click download button
Frontend -> Backend: tRPC documents.download(documentId)

Backend -> Database: Query DocumentUpload.storage_path
Database --> Backend: Return path

Backend -> StorageService: Generate signed URL (1-hour expiry)
StorageService --> Backend: Return signed URL

Backend --> Frontend: Return URL
Frontend -> Seller: Trigger download via signed URL

== Daily Expiry Check ==
ExpiryMonitor -> Database: Find documents expiring in 30 days
Database --> ExpiryMonitor: Return matching documents

loop For Each Expiring Document
  ExpiryMonitor -> Database: Check if alert_sent_30days = false
  alt Alert Not Sent
    ExpiryMonitor -> NotificationService: Send 30-day expiry alert
    NotificationService --> Seller: Email: "Document expires in 30 days"
    ExpiryMonitor -> Database: Update alert_sent_30days = true
  end
end

@enduml
